.TH "overlay_apply_node" 9 "overlay_apply_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
overlay_apply_node \- Merges a node into the base device tree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" overlay_apply_node
.BI "(void *fdt "  ","
.BI "int target "  ","
.BI "void *fdto "  ","
.BI "int node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fdt" 12
Base Device Tree blob
.IP "target" 12
Node offset in the base device tree to apply the fragment to
.IP "fdto" 12
Device tree overlay blob
.IP "node" 12
Node offset in the overlay holding the changes to merge
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBoverlay_apply_node\fP merges a node into a target base device tree
node pointed.

This is part of the final step in the device tree overlay
application process, when all the phandles have been adjusted and
resolved and you just have to merge overlay into the base device
tree.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success
Negative error code on failure
